(67430, 'The Final Phase (The Space Museum, Part Four)', 766, '<p>The TARDIS jumps a time track and the travellers arrive on the planet Xeros. There they discover their own future selves displayed as exhibits in a museum established as a monument to the galactic conquests of the warlike Morok invaders who now rule the planet. When time shifts back to normal, they realise that they must do everything they can to avert this potential future.</p><p>Vicki helps the native Xerons obtain arms and revolt against the Moroks. The revolution succeeds and the travellers go on their way, confident that the future has been changed.</p>', 29, 2, '1965-05-15', 'http://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/22/56256.jpg', 'http://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/67430/doctor-who-2x29-the-final-phase-the-space-museum-part-four'),
(67431, 'The Executioners (The Chase, Part One)', 766, '<p>The travellers learn from the Time-Space Visualiser taken from theMoroks'' museum that Daleks equipped with their own time machine are on their trail with orders to exterminate them. They flee in the TARDIS.</p><p>The chase begins on the desert planet Aridius and takes in a number of stopping-off points, including a spooky haunted house which is actually a futuristic fun-fair attraction.</p><p>Eventually both time machines arrive on the jungle planet Mechanus, where the Daleks try to infiltrate and kill the Doctor''s party with a robotic double of him. The travellers are taken prisoner by the Mechonoids — robots sent some fifty years earlier to prepare landing sites for human colonists who never arrived — and meet Steven Taylor, a stranded astronaut who has been the Mechonoids'' captive for the past two years.</p><p>The Daleks and the Mechonoids engage in a fierce battle which ends in their mutual destruction. The Doctor''s party seizes this opportunity to escape. The Doctor reluctantly helps Ian and Barbara to use the Daleks'' time machine to return home.</p>', 30, 2, '1965-05-22', 'http://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/22/56257.jpg', 'http://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/67431/doctor-who-2x30-the-executioners-the-chase-part-one'),
(67432, 'The Death of Time (The Chase, Part Two)', 766, '<p>The travellers learn from the Time-Space Visualiser taken from theMoroks'' museum that Daleks equipped with their own time machine are on their trail with orders to exterminate them. They flee in the TARDIS.</p><p>The chase begins on the desert planet Aridius and takes in a number of stopping-off points, including a spooky haunted house which is actually a futuristic fun-fair attraction.</p><p>Eventually both time machines arrive on the jungle planet Mechanus, where the Daleks try to infiltrate and kill the Doctor''s party with a robotic double of him. The travellers are taken prisoner by the Mechonoids — robots sent some fifty years earlier to prepare landing sites for human colonists who never arrived — and meet Steven Taylor, a stranded astronaut who has been the Mechonoids'' captive for the past two years.</p><p>The Daleks and the Mechonoids engage in a fierce battle which ends in their mutual destruction. The Doctor''s party seizes this opportunity to escape. The Doctor reluctantly helps Ian and Barbara to use the Daleks'' time machine to return home.</p>', 31, 2, '1965-05-29', 'http://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/22/56258.jpg', 'http://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/67432/doctor-who-2x31-the-death-of-time-the-chase-part-two'),
(67433, 'Flight through Eternity (The Chase, Part Three)', 766, '<p>The travellers learn from the Time-Space Visualiser taken from theMoroks'' museum that Daleks equipped with their own time machine are on their trail with orders to exterminate them. They flee in the TARDIS.</p><p>The chase begins on the desert planet Aridius and takes in a number of stopping-off points, including a spooky haunted house which is actually a futuristic fun-fair attraction.</p><p>Eventually both time machines arrive on the jungle planet Mechanus, where the Daleks try to infiltrate and kill the Doctor''s party with a robotic double of him. The travellers are taken prisoner by the Mechonoids — robots sent some fifty years earlier to prepare landing sites for human colonists who never arrived — and meet Steven Taylor, a stranded astronaut who has been the Mechonoids'' captive for the past two years.</p><p>The Daleks and the Mechonoids engage in a fierce battle which ends in their mutual destruction. The Doctor''s party seizes this opportunity to escape. The Doctor reluctantly helps Ian and Barbara to use the Daleks'' time machine to return home.</p>', 32, 2, '1965-06-05', NULL, 'http://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/67433/doctor-who-2x32-flight-through-eternity-the-chase-part-three');
