(67462, 'War of God (The Massacre of St Bartholomew''s Eve, Part One)', 766, '<p><i><b>Missing episode</b></i></p><p>The TARDIS materialises in Paris in the year 1572 and the Doctor decides to visit the famous apothecary Charles Preslin. Steven, meanwhile, is befriended by a group of Huguenots from the household of the Protestant Admiral de Coligny. Having rescued a young serving girl, Anne Chaplet, from some pursuing guards, the Huguenots gain their first inkling of a heinous plan being hatched at the command of the Catholic Queen Mother,Catherine de Medici.</p>', 22, 3, '1966-02-05', 'http://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/22/56288.jpg', 'http://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/67462/doctor-who-3x22-war-of-god-the-massacre-of-st-bartholomews-eve-part-one'),
